Why people fail at New Year’s resolutions! 

BECAUSE THEY’RE HARD

You’re literally re-wiring your brain to do something completely new or to stop doing something that’s a habit for you. 

They good news is we’re 19 days into the new year and some neuron plasticity models show that you can develop a habit as quickly as 21 days. 

That means it becomes easier. People get lost in the struggle of laying down that new framework because your body is used to comfort or whatever you were doing before! 

Keep going! Remember it gets easier! 

#makelifetap #davefoxceo #newyearsresolutions #motivation

Discipline is the ability to sacrifice what you want now for what you want most. 

This means conditioning your Mind and Body to do what you want not the other way around. For example I workout really early and get up at 5:00am. 

When I started doing this the alarm would go off and I would want to sleep in (what I wanted at that moment) but I know what I want most in this area of my life is to be healthy, be in shape and not have that ritual interfere with my family time. So if I’m sacrificing what I want now for what I want most early workouts were my best option. 

This is the skill to cultivate and a super power to achieving what you want in life! 

Secondly, you better be crystal clear in what you want most! 

Let’s go! 

#davefoxceo #makelifetap #speakingtomyself

📢📢I’ve noticed a lot of people talking about a 4 day work week on Linkedin and the study that occurred in the UK. This is my opinion on the matter.

I looked at the study and have piloted this personally in my own life and I don’t think this is a longterm benefit. Of course everyone is going to love having an extra day off and report better well being etc. in the short term.

But too often we sacrifice short term benefit for long term disaster. Every time I’ve personally or seen people choose a road that is easy and more comfortable over a road that is more difficult and challenging the results don’t make sense long term. Growth occurs when we’re challenged not when we try to make things easier.

Two quotes that resonate with my feelings on this:

1. Jim Rohn - “Don’t wish it was easier wish you were better. Don’t wish for less problems wish for more skills. Don’t wish for less challenge wish for more wisdom”

2. Jack Welch - “There’s no such thing as Work Life Balance, there are work life choices and you make them and they have consequences.”

Those are my thoughts I’d love to hear yours,

#work #wellbeing #worklifebalance #4dayworkweek #makelifetap #davefoxceo

📢📢So it’s been a minute since my last one of these but I’m not going to share stuff that hasn’t personally impacted me. 

Every now and then I get these things I call “downloads” and what these are are simply new areas of awareness or insights to help me an other move forward in life.

We already have greatness in us so what is keeping that greatness from shining through?

🤖We’re all hardwired! Since infancy, our evolving brains sketch out intricate neural networks that craft our life’s experiences. Occasionally, luck favors some with exceptional ‘programming’, but that’s far from the norm. 🧠🌐

By the time we’re 35, a staggering 95% of our daily thoughts and experiences become repetitive cycles.🔄🕰️ Sound monotonous? It is. The game-changer? Reprogramming.

Changing this ingrained mental blueprint is no walk in the park - it demands conscious effort, meticulous observation, and a readiness to untangle the intricate web of our thoughts, beliefs, values, and emotions.🕸️💭 

It’s about questioning whether they serve you well at this stage of your life.✅❎ Once the self-awareness kicks in, that’s when the real work begins - the task of altering those thoughts, beliefs, values, and emotions.🔄

I’ve been on this transformative journey for almost 5 years. It’s complex, it’s grueling, but it’s the best time investment I’ve ever made.⏳💪

The world might define success with material things, but the real change begins within YOU. Because at the end of the day, wherever you go, there you are, and you are the root of your issues.🌱🔍

Sure, you can’t change everything in an instant, but remember, one defining moment CAN change everything.✨

Embark on this journey, it’s challenging but oh so worth it!🚀💯 #Reprogramming #MindsetShift #JourneyToSelf #makelifetap #davefoxceo

🚫 Words You Need to Remove From Your Life Part: 1 🚫

💥 First Word: “Should” 💥

❌ When people use the word “should,” they’re unknowingly arguing with reality, asserting that things should be different simply because they don’t align with their preferences. It’s like tossing out a statement of dissatisfaction, demonstrating an ungrateful mindset towards the way things are. 🤔

🙅‍♂️ But here’s the thing: gratitude is the ultimate state of receivership. When we’re ungrateful, we block ourselves from experiencing the abundance and positivity that life has to offer. By fixating on what should be, we blind ourselves to the beauty of what actually is. 😌

⛔️ So, let’s break free from the shackles of “should” and embrace a transformative shift in perspective. Instead of dwelling on what could or should have been, let’s focus on cultivating gratitude for what already exists in our lives. 🙌

✨ When we replace “should” with appreciation, magical transformations unfold. We open ourselves up to new possibilities and find contentment in the present moment. By embracing gratitude, we become conscious co-creators of our reality, attracting more joy, abundance, and fulfillment. ✨

🌟 Therefore, let’s pledge to eliminate the word “should” from our vocabulary and infuse our thoughts and conversations with gratitude. Let’s embrace the power of acceptance and surrender, trusting the plan that is unfolding. 🌌

#PositiveVibesOnly #GratitudeMindset #WordsToBanish #NoMoreShoulds #EmbraceAcceptance #davefoxceo #makelifetap 🚫🙅‍♀️🌟✨🌌

🚫 Words You Need to Remove From Your Life Part: 2 🚫

💥 Second Word: “Try” 💥

❌ When it comes to making plans or pursuing goals, using the word “try” sets the stage for potential disappointment. If someone says they’ll “try” to make it to an event, chances are they won’t show up. 🙅‍♀️

🔐 The truth is, using “try” subconsciously places limitations on what we can achieve. Successful people don’t “try,” they empower themselves with phrases like “I’m gonna do it” or “I’m gonna make it happen.” They embrace the mindset that if it’s meant to be, it’s up to them. 💪🌟

⛔️ By eliminating “try” from your life, you shatter the barriers that hold you back and drastically increase your odds of success. It’s about taking ownership of your actions and embracing a mindset of determination and resilience. 🚀

🔥 So, let’s banish “try” from our vocabulary. Replace it with empowering phrases that ignite your inner fire. Embrace the power of “I will” and watch your dreams transform into reality. Remember, you have the strength within you to make it happen! Don’t try, do! 💥💪🌟

#WordsToBanish #EliminateTry #EmpowerYourself #NoMoreLimitations #SuccessMindset #davefoxceo #makelifetap 🔐❌⛔️🔥💥💪🌟

🚫 Words You Need to Remove From Your Life Part: 3 🚫

💥 Third Word: “Can’t” 💥

❌ Ah, the infamous “can’t” — a word that shackles our potential and robs us of our power. It’s time to break free from its suffocating grip and embrace the limitless realm of possibilities. Let’s unleash the rebel within and banish “can’t” from our vocabulary. 🔥💪

🚀 When we utter “can’t,” we surrender before even trying. It’s a self-imposed limitation that keeps us trapped in our comfort zones, preventing us from reaching new heights. But here’s the secret: we hold the key to our own liberation. 💥🗝️

✨ Instead of succumbing to the limitations of “can’t,” let’s choose empowering phrases like “I choose not to,” “I haven’t mastered it yet,” or “I’ll find a way.” By embracing these words of possibility, we reclaim our power and open doors to growth, resilience, and achievement. 💫🌟

💪 Remember, the power lies within you. Embrace the belief that you are capable of great things. By eliminating “can’t,” you tap into your inner strength, paving the way for remarkable transformations. The choice is yours, my fearless warrior. ✊😎

🌠 So, let’s embrace a mindset of endless potential. Replace “can’t” with empowering phrases and watch as the world unfolds before you. You have the power to overcome, evolve, and create your own destiny. Let’s rewrite the narrative, one powerful word at a time. 💥💪🌟

#WordsToBanish #UnleashYourPower #makelifetap #davefoxceo #fitabundantaligned #LimitlessPotential #ChooseEmpowerment #ReclaimYourStrength 🔥🚀💥🌟✨✊😎

🗣️Almost half way through 2023, this is a good time to evaluate and make some tweaks. 🗣️

Do you ever feel like your goals and dreams just slipping through your fingers? 🙌🌬️ A lot of people think they’re committed but maybe it’s time for a commitment reality check! 💯👀

‼️If you’re truly committed to the outcome there should be evidence of the following 3 things‼️

1️⃣ Consistent Effort: True commitment means you’re in the trenches, pushing through every day, rain or shine. No matter the hurdles, you’re hustling and building the habits and disciplines it’s going to take to succeed!💪⏰

2️⃣ Sacrifices: You’re not just dreaming, you’re DOING. That might mean missing out on small joys for the big win. Wanting something and being willing to give up the “fun” stuff to make it happen are two completely different things. How much are you willing to give? 🎁🏆

3️⃣ Values Alignment: This isn’t just any goal, it’s YOUR goal, deeply connected to your core values and believes. Are you seeing a reflection of yourself in your journey? If not there may be an alignment issue 💙🔄

It’s not about the setback, it’s about the comeback. If things don’t seem to be working. Check your commitment, and let’s turn those dreams into reality! We still have 6 months left this year. 

We don’t get what we want in life, WE GET WHAT WE COMMIT TO! #RealityCheck #CommitmentIsKey #fitabundantaligned #davefoxceo #makelifetap🔐💫

🚫 ‘Reasons People Fail To Achieve Their Goals: Part 1 - Not Following Instructions’ 🚫

Hey team, we’re rolling into Day 2 of our 🗓️ July Habit Challenge! As we journey into this month of transformation, I want to peel back the layers on something critical. ‘Why People Fail at Their Goals’. 👎 

Today, we’re tackling the first misstep many make: Not Following Instructions. 📝 Yes, it’s as straightforward as it sounds, yet often overlooked. For our challenge, we set a clear goal: Add or subtract one habit from your life for a month. Then comment on mine or @befoxy daily post that you achieved what you set out to do or not do for the day. 🔄 It’s about commitment, consistency, and follow-through! 💪

Stumbling a bit? Remember, it’s not the complexity of the task, but the consistency of action that makes the difference. 🎯 The daily grind is where real change happens. One small step, one day at a time, that’s the ticket to success! 🔝

Speaking of instructions, let’s discuss something I’ve noticed in the past - modifications of @AndyFrisella ‘s 75 Hard Challenge 🏋️‍♂️IT’S THE SAME ISSUE. People are bending the rules and creating their own versions. But let me tell you, that’s not how it works! Each rule in the challenge was designed with PURPOSE to turn you into a beast. 🗣️You know why Mondays sting⁉️ 

📢Because  most people have been hitting the ‘pause’ button all weekend. It’s not about work - it’s about working on YOU‼️

Sleeping in, staying out late, veering off the diet - all justified because ‘it’s the weekend.’ COMMON 🤦‍♂️

This inconsistent rhythm disrupts our progress and is the cause for the Monday blues. 💤🍔🍻

🗣️On top of that your subconscious knows the truth and some level regret and self disappointment are now sucking your energy like Count Dracula at a blood bank 🧛‍♂️

IF you’re committed to becoming the best version of yourself, the day of the week shouldn’t matter.✨ Your goals don’t take a break on Saturdays or Sundays, so why should you? 📈

Non-negotiable actions are key to constant growth. It’s these rituals that build us up, piece by piece, into the individuals we aspire to be. And they must happen, no matter what day it is.📌🚀 

You want to keep dreading Mondays? Keep using the weekend as your excuse. But if you’re ready to break the cycle and challenge the status quo, make every day count. Because in the journey of self-improvement, there’s no such thing as a ‘day off.’ 💪🔥

🔥🔥 BURNOUT: MYTH OR MINDSET? 🔥🔥

💥 Unleashing a controversial truth!

🤔 We’ve all heard the term “burnout” used to describe a state of exhaustion and overwhelm, but is it really an unavoidable fate, or is there more to the story?

🚀I DON’T BELIEVE BURNOUT IS REAL‼️

Looking forward to the comments on this😂. What we call “Burnout” is a combination of two things. 

1️⃣ Over fixation on the outcome that your seeking. Typically this is accompanied by a story of how that outcome “should” come to fruition. 

And 

2️⃣ Entitlement: yup, the “E” word. That one stings🐝. Entitlement is when we think we deserve something NOW. 

🌟 Picture this: waking up every single day, fully in love with the process and the journey. Embracing each step as an opportunity for growth and self-improvement, without fixating solely on the end destination. Knowing that it will come but not really caring how. 1 step at a time. 🚶

What if we channel our energy into becoming the best version of ourselves, without demanding instant results😂

🗣️ I’LL TELL you what will happen. You will never “Burnout”⁉️

🔥 So, here’s the hard truth: what people call “burnout” isn’t an inescapable force; it’s a mindset. 🤯 When we adopt a mindset of growth, gratitude, and discipline, we become unstoppable forces of positivity and determination. 💥

So stop being entitled. Love the process and enjoy the journey. It’s NOT instant‼️
